After crossing the border into Canada,  road signs change into metric units; distances are in kilometres and speed limits in km per hour. One mile is 1.609 km so multiply what you see on the road signs by 5/8 to get its equivalent in miles e.g. 40 km = 25 miles and 100 km/h = 62.5 mph.  If you are driving a US-model vehicle into Canada, the speedometer will have US units on top or outward while metric units are below or inward.

As of 2013, drivers of US registered vehicles in Canada are no longer required to carry a separate Canadian insurance document.

